The bug in your code is that you are multiplying `first.quantity` by itself
itself when calculating the `subtotal`, instead of using its real value whi
which can be obtained from `parseNumber(first.unitPrice)`. You need to chan
change your calculation line as follows to fix this error:

```tundra
val subtotal = parseNumber(first.quantity) * parseNumber(first.unitPrice);
```

Therefore, the corrected program will be:

```tundra
val order = {
  lines: [
    { sku: "A", quantity: "2", unitPrice: "5" },
    { sku: "B", quantity: "1", unitPrice: "4" }
  ]
};

val first = order.lines[0];
val second = order.lines[1];
val subtotal = parseNumber(first.quantity) * parseNumber(first.unitPrice);

print(subtotal);
```
